---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Oakdene House Foundation"
  description="Oakdene House Foundation Privacy Policy — how we collect, use, store and protect your personal information in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 and the Australian Privacy Principles."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="legal-hero" aria-label="Privacy Policy">
    <div class="container legal-hero__content">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb__sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <span aria-current="page">Privacy Policy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DOCUMENT BODY -->
  <section class="section" aria-label="Privacy Policy content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="doc-wrap">

        <!-- Dates -->
        <div class="doc-meta">
          <p><em>Last updated: [Launch date to be inserted]</em></p>
          <p><em>Effective from: [Launch date to be inserted]</em></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Table of contents -->
        <nav class="doc-toc" aria-label="Page contents">
          <p class="doc-toc__heading">Contents</p>
          <ol class="doc-toc__list">
            <li><a href="#section-1">1. Who we are</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-2">2. What personal information we collect</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-3">3. Why we collect personal information</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-4">4. Payment information (donations)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-5">5. How we store and protect your information</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-6">6. When we share your information</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-7">7. Cookies and website tracking</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-8">8. Your rights</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-9">9. Keeping information current</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-10">10. Complaints</a></li>
            <li><a href="#section-11">11. Changes to this policy</a></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <!-- Intro -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <p>Oakdene House Foundation ("Oakdene", "we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting the privacy of people who visit our website, contact us, access our services, or engage with us in any way. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, disclose, and protect your personal information.</p>
          <p>We handle personal information in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs). As a registered health service provider we also comply with the My Health Records Act 2012 and relevant state health records legislation where applicable.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-1">
          <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
          <div class="doc-address">
            <p>Oakdene House Foundation</p>
            <p>ABN 90 151 950 926</p>
            <p>Registered Australian charity (ACNC)</p>
            <p>29 Vine Street, Fairfield NSW 2165</p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:+61287170999">(02) 8717 0999</a></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:admin@oakdenehouse.org.au">admin@oakdenehouse.org.au</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-2">
          <h2>2. What personal information we collect</h2>
          <p>We only collect personal information that is reasonably necessary for one or more of our functions or activities. The type of information we collect depends on how you interact with us.</p>

          <h3>2.1 Information you give us directly</h3>
          <p>When you contact us, submit a form, attend our centre, or access our services, we may collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Contact details: name, phone number, email address, postal address</li>
            <li>Demographic information: date of birth, gender, preferred language, cultural background</li>
            <li>Health and wellbeing information: presenting concerns, mental health history, substance use history, medical conditions, medications, diagnoses (where relevant to the support we provide)</li>
            <li>Life circumstances: housing situation, employment, family situation, legal or justice involvement</li>
            <li>Emergency contact details: name and contact details of a trusted person</li>
            <li>Referrer details: if someone else refers you to us, we collect their details as well</li>
            <li>Payment information: if you make a donation, we collect information needed to process the payment (see section 4)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.2 Information we collect when you use our website</h3>
          <p>When you visit oakdenehouse.org.au we may collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>IP address and approximate location (city / region)</li>
            <li>Browser type and device information</li>
            <li>Pages visited, time spent, and referring website</li>
            <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies (see section 7)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.3 Information from third parties</h3>
          <p>We may receive personal information about you from:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Referring agencies (community corrections, legal services, health services, other community organisations)</li>
            <li>Family members or friends who refer you with your consent</li>
            <li>Healthcare providers involved in your care, with your consent</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.4 Sensitive information</h3>
          <p>Some of the information we collect is "sensitive information" under the Privacy Act — including health information, information about race or ethnicity, religious beliefs, criminal record, and sexual orientation.</p>
          <p><strong>We only collect sensitive information with your consent and only where it is directly relevant to the support we provide.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-3">
          <h2>3. Why we collect personal information</h2>
          <p>We collect, hold, use, and disclose your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>To provide counselling, support, and community programs</li>
            <li>To assess suitability for our programs and make appropriate referrals</li>
            <li>To contact you about appointments, programs, or follow-up support</li>
            <li>To respond to enquiries submitted through our website or contact channels</li>
            <li>To process volunteer applications</li>
            <li>To process donations and issue receipts</li>
            <li>To improve our services and train our staff</li>
            <li>To fulfil our legal, regulatory, and funding obligations (including reporting to the ACNC and government funders)</li>
            <li>To send you newsletters or updates, where you have opted in</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-4">
          <h2>4. Payment information (donations)</h2>
          <p>Donations made through our website are processed by Stripe Payments Australia Pty Ltd (<a href="https://stripe.com/au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stripe.com/au</a>). Your credit card or bank details are entered directly into Stripe's secure payment system — Oakdene does not see, store, or have access to your full card details.</p>
          <p>Stripe is PCI DSS Level 1 compliant (the highest industry standard) and acts as the data controller for the card transaction itself. Stripe's privacy policy is available at <a href="https://stripe.com/au/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stripe.com/au/privacy</a>.</p>
          <p>Oakdene does receive and retain:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>The donor's name, email, and postal address (for receipting)</li>
            <li>The donation amount, date, and frequency (one-off or recurring)</li>
            <li>A confirmation that the payment succeeded</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We keep this information for the period required under Australian tax and charity law (currently 7 years).</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 5 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-5">
          <h2>5. How we store and protect your information</h2>
          <p>Your personal information is stored in secure cloud-based systems and, where relevant, in physical case files held at our centre. We take reasonable steps to protect your information from:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Unauthorised access or disclosure</li>
            <li>Loss, misuse, or modification</li>
            <li>Interference</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Our protections include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Password-protected and role-restricted access to case management systems</li>
            <li>Encrypted storage and transmission (HTTPS)</li>
            <li>Staff training on privacy and confidentiality</li>
            <li>Physical security of the centre and its records</li>
            <li>Regular review of access and security practices</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Some service providers we use (e.g. Microsoft 365, Jotform, Stripe) may store information on servers outside Australia. We only use providers who comply with equivalent privacy standards and the APPs.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 6 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-6">
          <h2>6. When we share your information</h2>
          <p><strong>We will not sell, trade, or rent your personal information. We will only disclose your information:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>With your consent — for example, to a doctor, another service provider, or a family member you have nominated</li>
            <li>To service providers who help us operate — including IT providers, payment processors, email providers, and cloud storage providers, under confidentiality obligations</li>
            <li>To funders and regulators — in de-identified or aggregated form for reporting purposes (individual identities are not shared)</li>
            <li>Where required or authorised by law — for example, under a court order, subpoena, or mandatory reporting obligation</li>
            <li>In an emergency — where we reasonably believe there is a serious threat to the life, health, or safety of any person</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 7 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-7">
          <h2>7. Cookies and website tracking</h2>
          <p>Our website uses cookies and similar technologies to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Make the site work properly (essential cookies)</li>
            <li>Understand how visitors use the site so we can improve it (analytics cookies)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect some features of the site.</p>
          <p>We do not use cookies for advertising or to track you across other websites.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 8 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-8">
          <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
          <p>Under the Privacy Act and APPs you have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Access the personal information we hold about you</li>
            <li>Correct information that is inaccurate, out of date, or incomplete</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent for us to use your information (where use is based on consent)</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your information, subject to our legal record-keeping obligations</li>
            <li>Make a complaint about how we have handled your information (see section 10)</li>
            <li>Remain anonymous or use a pseudonym when dealing with us where lawful and practicable — please note this may not be possible for clinical services</li>
          </ul>
          <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the details in section 1.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 9 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-9">
          <h2>9. Keeping information current</h2>
          <p>We take reasonable steps to make sure the information we hold is accurate, complete, and up to date. Please let us know if any of your contact details or circumstances change.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 10 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-10">
          <h2>10. Complaints</h2>
          <p>If you have a concern about how we have handled your personal information, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> first at:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Email: <a href="mailto:admin@oakdenehouse.org.au">admin@oakdenehouse.org.au</a></li>
            <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+61287170999">(02) 8717 0999</a></li>
            <li>Post: PO Box 988, Fairfield NSW 1860</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We take privacy complaints seriously and will acknowledge your complaint within 5 business days and respond in full within 30 days.</p>
          <p>If you are not satisfied with our response, you can contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC):</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Website: <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">oaic.gov.au</a></li>
            <li>Phone: <a href="tel:1300363992">1300 363 992</a></li>
            <li>Post: GPO Box 5288, Sydney NSW 2001</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 11 -->
        <div class="doc-section" id="section-11">
          <h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The most current version will always be available on our website, with the "Last updated" date shown at the top.</p>
          <p>Material changes will be communicated via a notice on our website or direct communication to clients where appropriate.</p>
          <p><em>This Privacy Policy is written in plain language to help you understand your rights. It is not legal advice. If you have specific questions about your personal information, please contact us directly.</em></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ---- Hero ---- */
  .legal-hero {
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    padding-block: 52px 44px;
  }

  .legal-hero h1 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Document wrapper ---- */
  .doc-wrap {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  /* ---- Dates metadata ---- */
  .doc-meta {
    padding: 18px 22px;
    background-color: var(--color-tint);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-secondary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-card) var(--radius-card) 0;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }

  .doc-meta p {
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .doc-meta p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Table of contents ---- */
  .doc-toc {
    background-color: var(--color-tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 22px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 52px;
  }

  .doc-toc__heading {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .doc-toc__list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 7px;
    padding-left: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .doc-toc__list a {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .doc-toc__list a:hover {
    color: var(--color-link-hover);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* ---- Document sections ---- */
  .doc-section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .doc-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .doc-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-secondary);
    scroll-margin-top: 88px;
  }

  .doc-section h3 {
    margin-top: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    scroll-margin-top: 88px;
  }

  .doc-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.72;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .doc-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .doc-section ul,
  .doc-section ol {
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .doc-section li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 7px;
  }

  .doc-section a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .doc-section a:hover {
    color: var(--color-link-hover);
  }

  /* ---- Address / who we are block ---- */
  .doc-address {
    background-color: var(--color-tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .doc-address p {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .doc-address p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .doc-address a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .doc-address a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
